_PRINTF(3)                Library functions                _PRINTF(3)

NAME
       _printf - minimal printf implementation for Holberton project

SYNOPSIS
       #include "holberton.h"

       int _printf(const char *format, ...);

DESCRIPTION
       _printf formats and sends output to the standard output (stdout).
       This implementation supports the following conversion specifiers:
           %c  - print single character
           %s  - print string (NULL prints "(null)")
           %%  - print percent sign
           %d, %i - print signed decimal integer

RETURN VALUE
       On success, _printf returns the number of characters printed (excluding
       the terminating null byte). On error, -1 is returned.

NOTES
       Output is performed using the write(2) system call. No support is
       provided for flags, field width, precision, or length modifiers.

AUTHOR
       Implemented for Holberton project.
